place_info.title: ANTICA OSTERIA CARNEYA
place_info.address: 市ヶ谷ＮＨビル 1F 3-6 Minamiyamabushicho, Shinjuku City, Tokyo 162-0854, Japan

reviews.snippet:
全体的に味付けは濃いかも。
またメニュー名と実際の料理に違いを感じる。
短角牛のミートソースは良くあるミートソースとは別モノ。
例えるならコンビーフを手で解した塊がゴロゴロパスタと和えたモノで、肉肉しいさは強め。
期待したキャベツソテーのハンバーガーはタイトルに騙された期待外れの品。
てっきりザク切りキャベツのソテーが挟まれているのかとハンズを外したらちょっとだけのザワークラウトっぽい味の濃いものだった。
その他のサービスや料理に関しては他の方々のコメント通りかな。
reviews.translated_snippet:
The seasoning is a bit strong overall.
I also noticed a difference between the menu name and the actual dish.
The shorthorn beef meat sauce is different to your typical meat sauce.
To put it in perspective, it's like hand-shredded chunks of corned beef mixed with chunky pasta, and it has a strong meaty flavor.
The sauteed cabbage hamburger, which I was looking forward to, was a disappointment, as I was fooled by the title.
I thought it would be filled with shredded cabbage, but when I removed the handle, it had a strong flavor similar to sauerkraut.
As for the rest of the service and food, I think other people's comments are correct.

place_info.address: 3 Chome-28-10 Ueno, Taito City, Tokyo 110-0005, Japan

reviews.snippet:
餃子はモッチモチで焼きめがサクサクで超美味。
チャーハンは有名らしく、みんな餃子と一緒に頼んでいるが、塩気が絶妙な感じだった。冷めると塩っぱい感じがするので冷めないうちに食べましょう。
ついでに昭和風焼きそばとピリ辛ナス炒めも頼んだが、調理する皆さんは高齢で炒め過ぎ感が否めないし、味付けは土地柄なのか塩味が強く味付けは濃い。
しかしどれをとっても出来立ての料理は最高だった。
reviews.translated_snippet:
The gyoza were chewy and crispy, and absolutely delicious.
The fried rice is apparently famous, and everyone orders it along with the gyoza, and it had just the right amount of saltiness. It gets too salty once it cools, so be sure to eat it while it's still hot.
We also ordered Showa-style fried noodles and spicy stir-fried eggplant, but the cooks were elderly and tended to overcook the food, and the seasoning was strong and salty, perhaps due to the local flavor.
But no matter what we ordered, the freshly cooked food was excellent.

place_info.title: Curry and Pasta Tacurry
place_info.address: 70 Ichigayayakuojimachi, Shinjuku City, Tokyo 162-0063, Japan

reviews.snippet:
初めて伺いましたが、まず驚いたのが、テーブルとカウンターに昔喫茶店によくあったガラスの灰皿があったこと。

ランチは既存のメニューから1種だけ50円引きしていた様子。

店主が自ら調理と配膳しておりワンオペ対応。

結構マッタリとした室内空間は落ち着いた雰囲気。

肝心のメニューだが、カツカレーはちょっと少なめのカツに対して、やや小さめのお皿に約2/3ぐらいの盛り付けたご飯にたっぷりの野菜を良く煮込んだルーがたっぷり。
出てきた時は少ないなと思ったけど、結構なボリュームだったし、ちょい辛めなので食欲マシマシで一気に食べてしまった。
ランチの付け合わせのサラダはザク切りレタスに輪切りのきゅーりにデルモンテにホールコーンを乗せて市販のごまドレをかけたもの。

珍しかったカレースパゲッティは意外と美味だった。
もしかしたらカレーカツスパゲッティを別注出来るかも。

あんな所にこんな昔っぽい飲食店があるのは貴重なお店でした。
次回は別注してみようかと思います。
reviews.translated_snippet:
It was my first time visiting, and the first thing that surprised me was the glass ashtrays on the tables and counter, the kind you'd often see in coffee shops back in the day.

It seems that one item from the existing menu was discounted by 50 yen for lunch.

The owner cooks and serves the food himself, so he can work alone.

The interior space has a fairly laid-back, calm atmosphere.

As for the main menu item, the katsu curry came with a small portion of katsu, served on a slightly small plate with about two-thirds of the rice filled and a generous amount of well-simmered vegetables in a sauce.

When it arrived, I thought it was a little small, but it was actually quite filling and a little spicy, so my appetite was whetted and I ate it all in one go.

The lunch side salad was made of roughly sliced ​​lettuce, sliced ​​cucumber, Del Monte corn, and whole corn, all topped with a commercially available sesame dressing.

The curry spaghetti, which was unusual, was surprisingly delicious.

You might even be able to order curry katsu spaghetti.

It was a rare find to find such an old-fashioned restaurant in such a place.
I think I'll try ordering something special next time.

place_info.address: 大和 富山店 6F 3 Chome-8-6 Sogawa, Toyama, 930-0083, Japan

reviews.snippet:
遅めのランチで唯一営業していたので寄ってみた先。
どうやら地元では老舗らしい。
ワンタン麺はその名の通り雲のような感じ。※上手く表現できない。
シンプルな味だったが他にも餃子やお米など実はこだわりがある。
また近くに本店があったので、営業時間間に合う人は本店で味わうのもいいのではないでしょうか。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I stopped by as it was the only place open for a late lunch.
It seems to be a well-established local restaurant.
The wonton noodles, as their name suggests, are like clouds. *I can't really describe it.
The flavor was simple, but they also put a lot of effort into their other dishes, such as their gyoza and rice.
The main store is also nearby, so if you can make it during opening hours, it might be a good idea to stop by there.

reviews.translated_snippet:
Parking in the free parking lot can be difficult if you don't know how to get in.
It's a one-way street.
There's a stylish cafe across the street, so it might be a good idea to stop by on your way home from visiting the shrine.
However, there are only a few parking spaces, so be sure to give up your parking space as soon as you've finished.

place_info.address: 3 Chome-9-2 Sogawa, Toyama, 930-0083, Japan

reviews.snippet:
色んなドーミインに泊まったけど、ここが最高だった。
決めては室内のお風呂は温泉が引いてあり、ボタン一つで温泉が出てくるし追出しも可。
知らない人と入浴するのを好まない人には最高なんじゃないかな。
あとはドーミインお約束の夜泣きそば。
ここは食事を見逃した人にフロントでお願いしたら、ご麺なさいと言うインスタントラーメンを貰える。
しかし夜鳴きそばが大盛り対応してるとは知らなかった。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I've stayed at a number of Dormi Inns, but this one was the best.
The best thing about it is that the in-room bath has hot spring water, which comes out with the push of a button and can also be turned off.
I think it's perfect for people who don't like bathing with strangers.
Also, there's the Yonaki Soba, a Dormi Inn staple.
If you miss your meal here, you can ask at the front desk and they'll give you a bowl of instant ramen called Gomennasai.
However, I didn't know that they offered large portions of Yonaki Soba.

translated_details.rooms: The indoor bath is also a hot spring.

reviews.translated_snippet:
There's not much parking and it gets crowded.
There are probably various reasons for this, but I guess it can't be helped since it's an inexpensive place with a great view.
Also, the fountain show was worth seeing and interesting.
It's no wonder Starbucks is crowded.

reviews.translated_snippet:
The facility in front is currently a factory.
They are currently open for business at the back of the building.
For meals there is a fast food-style counter and a diner-style restaurant.
They seem to specialize in white shrimp burgers, but I didn't see anyone eating them.

I recommend the whole thing, including the department store.

place_info.title: Sekihara pasta & wine
place_info.address: ハウス関原 10-12 Yochomachi, Shinjuku City, Tokyo 162-0055, Japan

reviews.snippet:
平日しかランチをやっていないので、やっと初めて行ってみた。
店内は広くは無いが開放的な２階建ての店内。
12時前に入ったら既にランチしている客が居て、満席直前だった。
ランチの肝心のパスタだが連れと一緒に２種類のパスタを頼んだがどれも1.8から1.9mmぐらいのスパゲッティ麺だったので食べ応えはあったけど、味付けは普通で、専門的な驚きや中毒になるような美味しさは無かったかな。
ボロネーゼを大盛りで頼んでみたが、通常サイズの盛り付けされる皿に盛り付けたのか、山盛り感はあったが皿の余白がない為か美味しそうに見えなかった。
一口目は振りかけていたバジルと思えるスパイスが気になった。
パスタが大盛りにしたせいなのか、ボロネーゼのミートソースは肉々しくしない。
ひき肉は粗めで少なめ。
全体的に悪い印象は無かったが、また行きたくなるよう感じはないけど、場所柄飲食店が少ないので食事済ませて外に出たら、数名並んでいた。
reviews.translated_snippet:
They only serve lunch on weekdays, so I finally went there for the first time.
The restaurant is not large, but it has an open two-story interior.
When we arrived just before 12 o'clock, there were already customers having lunch, and it was almost full.
As for the essential lunch dish, pasta, my companion and I ordered two types of pasta, both of which had spaghetti noodles about 1.8 to 1.9 mm thick, so they were filling, but the seasoning was average and there was nothing particularly surprising or addictively delicious.
I ordered a large portion of Bolognese, but it was served on a regular-sized plate, so although it seemed like a mountain of food, it didn't look very appetizing, perhaps because there was no white space on the plate.
At my first bite, I was bothered by the spices that seemed to be basil sprinkled on top.
Perhaps because the pasta was served in a large portion, the meat sauce in the Bolognese was not too meaty.
The minced meat was coarse and there was not much of it. Overall, I didn't have a bad impression, but I don't feel like I want to go back. However, because of the location, there aren't many restaurants, so when I went outside after finishing my meal, there were several people waiting in line.

place_info.title: Ramen Kagetsu Arashi
place_info.address: 2 Chome-14-4 Yanagibashi, Taito City, Tokyo 111-0052, Japan

reviews.snippet:
妙高市の有名なとん汁屋の期間限定とん汁ラーメンに出会えて嬉しかった。
しかし豆腐と豚バラは二切れずつ。
これじゃとん汁じゃないよっ。

あと餃子は皮が美味しく焼き加
減絶妙。

しかし何故半熟たまごになったんだろう。
私はこの半熟が苦手だ。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I was happy to come across the limited-time tonjiru ramen from a famous tonjiru shop in Myoko City.
However, there were two pieces each of tofu and pork belly.
This is not pork soup.

Also, the gyoza skin is deliciously grilled.
Exquisite reduction.

But why did it become a half-boiled egg?
I don't like this half-boiled food.

place_info.title: Harada Farm
place_info.address: 1294 Yokozukamachi, Numata, Gunma 378-0002, Japan

reviews.snippet:
施設の中にある軽食レストラン。
この辺でチェーン店以外で朝食事できるところを探してたどり着いた先。
午前中だったせいなのかモツ料理は売れ切れ。
訪問した時はうどんと牛丼のみ販売。
うどんは土地柄濃い目の汁。
牛丼は濃いめの味付けに玉ねぎとこんにゃくが入っていて美味。
しかし付け合わせの味噌汁はインスタント生味噌に業務用の大きな湯沸かし器の蛇口でお湯を注ぐチープさ。
奥から見える厨房には業務用のレトルトパックが置いてあり、手作り感が無い料理だったかもしれないが、学食っぽい感じを思い出しそれなりに美味しかった。
reviews.translated_snippet:
A snack restaurant located within the facility.
I ended up here while looking for a non-chain place to have breakfast in the area.
Perhaps because it was mid-morning, the offal dishes were sold out.
When I visited, they only had udon and beef bowls available.
The udon had a strong broth, typical of the region.
The beef bowl was richly flavored with onions and konjac and was delicious.
However, the miso soup that came with it was cheap, made with instant raw miso and hot water poured from the tap of a large commercial water heater.
There were commercial-grade retort pouches in the kitchen, visible from the back, and the food may not have had a homemade feel to it, but it reminded me of a school cafeteria atmosphere and was still quite tasty.

place_info.title: みんなの畑レストラン 収穫祭
place_info.address: Japan, 〒378-0005 Gunma, Numata, Kuyaharamachi, 327-4 ソナタリュー施設内

reviews.snippet:
レストラン、温泉、カフェ、フィットネスジムなどの施設が集まったおしゃれな施設。
あまり知られていないのか日曜日の昼間でもガラガラ。
肝心のレストランは地元の食材を使ったお洒落な料理。
食材と調理はこだわり感が伝わったけど、豚の料理はちっちゃい塊の肉をスライスし、ライスもしょぼすぎた量で満足感は全くなし。
サラダだけはボリュームもあり色鮮やかな見栄えでドレッシングの味はやさいの旨味を引き立てるものだった。
残念だったのは、作り手と食べ手をつなげるホールスタッフのレベルの低さ。
オススメの料理に対する説明不足や料理に添えているソースの説明が無い。値段と見栄えは原宿のレストランと同じだなって感じちゃうぐらい都会的な印象。
お店は兎も角、施設内には無料の足湯もあるから別の機会にまた沼田市に行くことがあれば寄りたい場所だったかな。
reviews.translated_snippet:
A stylish facility housing restaurants, hot springs, cafes, fitness gyms and more.
Perhaps it's not very well known, as it was empty even on a Sunday afternoon.
The restaurant itself served stylish cuisine made with local ingredients.
I could sense the care that went into the ingredients and cooking, but the pork dish was just tiny slices of meat and the rice was a meager portion, so it wasn't at all satisfying.
Only the salad was filling and colorful, and the dressing brought out the umami of the vegetables.
What was disappointing was the low level of the wait staff, who were meant to connect the cooks with the diners.
There was a lack of explanation for the recommended dishes and no description of the sauces that came with the dishes. The prices and presentation were so urban that it felt similar to a restaurant in Harajuku.
Regardless of the restaurant itself, there was also a free foot bath on site, so if I visit Numata City again on another occasion, it would be a place I'd like to visit.

reviews.snippet:
埼玉のラーメンチェーンが運営している温泉ホテルと中華レストラン。
色々なコメントが書かれているけど、実際に行ってみてタイミングや店員さんによって評価は様々だと思った。
チェックイン時に同性がおり、間違えて違う部屋の鍵を受け取ったら山側の部屋だった。
初めてだったので部屋に入って違うと気づき予約した川側へ変更。
窓から見える景色は川の向かいにある老朽化した旅館と廃墟のホテル。窓下は木々が生い茂っており川は見えないし虫は沢山飛んでいるので窓は開けられない状態。
しかし室内は広くて清潔感があってイコゴチ良し。
館内は入口で靴を脱いで裸足になる。館内や室内もスリッパは無くてレストランも当然裸足で勿論定員さんもだ。
兎に角、安いので予約は直ぐに埋まるけど、一回は泊まってみる価値のあるところだった。
reviews.translated_snippet:
: This hot spring hotel and Chinese restaurant is run by a ramen chain in Saitama.
There have been a variety of reviews, but after actually going there, I think the reviews vary depending on the timing and the staff.
When I checked in, there was a woman there and I mistakenly received a key for the wrong room, which turned out to be a mountain-facing room.
Since it was my first time, I realized it was the wrong room when I got inside and changed to the river-facing one I had reserved.
The view from the window was of a dilapidated inn and abandoned hotel across the river. The trees below were overgrown, obscuring the view of the river, and there were so many insects flying around that I couldn't open the window.
However, the room was spacious and clean, making it perfect for a night out.
You have to take your shoes off at the entrance to the building and go barefoot. There are no slippers inside the building or inside the room, and of course you have to go barefoot in the restaurant, including the staff.
In any case, it's cheap so reservations fill up quickly, but it's definitely worth staying there at least once.

reviews.translated_snippet:

However, although the soba noodles seem to have improved, they were still terrible.
At first glance, the thin, limp noodles looked like Maruchan's Green Tanuki Soba noodles had been stretched out.
The miso soup looked like miso soup, but was just a clear soup with no real flavor or broth.
When I ordered a la carte conger eel tempura, it was such a poorly fried dish that I wondered where the conger eel was in there.
It's good that they've improved, but I wish they hadn't changed the deliciousness of the past.
Well, the food was disappointing.
I probably won't be visiting Ten-Ya for a while 🤣

reviews.snippet:
神戸などにあるパールホテルの系列かと思って勘違い。
しかし朝食はバイキング形式で満足感がありお得。
場所柄駅前と言っても朝は食事できるところはホテル周辺にはないので。
肝心の室内は今回シングルベットツインの部屋を泊まったが、諸々シングルルームに無理やり仮設ベットを足したツイン仕様の為、足の踏み場もない狭い室内。
部屋での食事はベットの上。
冷蔵庫は仮設ベットに当たって全開に開けない有様。
そういう意味で1泊約1万で宿泊出来るんだから仕方がない。
駐車場も完備しているので、コスト重視の方にはおすすめかも。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I mistakenly thought it was a sister hotel to the Pearl Hotel in Kobe and other places.
However, the breakfast was a satisfying buffet, so it was good value.
Even though it's in front of the station, there are no places to eat in the morning around the hotel.
As for the interior, I stayed in a twin room with a single bed, but because it was a single room with a temporary bed added, it was a very cramped room with barely any room to walk.
Eating in the room was done on the bed.
The refrigerator was hitting the temporary bed so couldn't be opened all the way.
In that sense, it's understandable considering you can stay there for about 10,000 yen a night.
There is also a parking lot, so it might be recommended for those who are cost-conscious.

reviews.snippet:
店員さんにコックのお祖父ちゃんも愛想良くて良い感じのお店。
初めて伺ったのでGoogleマップでメニューチェックしたらお目当ての焼肉定食が無くてガッカリ。

常連さんらはどうやらナポリタン目当てらしく、次回は試してみたいお店でした。
reviews.translated_snippet:
The waiters and the chef's grandfather were all very friendly and it was a really nice restaurant.
It was my first time there so I checked the menu on Google Maps and was disappointed to see that the yakiniku set meal I was looking for wasn't there.
I had the pork ginger instead, which was made to taste like a steak like the ones I had in old Western restaurants.
The regulars seemed to be there for the Neapolitan pasta, so it's a restaurant I'd like to try next time.

place_info.title: 和の牛 かた山
place_info.address: Japan, 〒162-0061 Tokyo, Shinjuku City, Ichigayayanagicho, 11 伊藤ビル 102

reviews.snippet:
ランチメニューのハラミステーキを連れと一緒に頼みましたが、サラダと味噌汁など盛り付けにバラツキが大きい。
味噌汁は正直言ってしょっぱすぎで具は煮込み過ぎで酷い。
他の人は気にせずに食せるのに驚く。
昔はランチでも個々にロースターを用意して焼肉が楽しめたようだが、今回行ったタイミングでは全て鉄板焼スタイルで、タイミングが悪いと店内は煙に包まれるお店。幸いにも店員さんは皆さん明るく応対も優しく気持ちよく食事はできるが、環境と味付けでちょっと減点。
ランチメニューは殆どが鉄板で出てくるけど、全て肉も野菜も焦げ焦げまで火を通して出てくる始末。
折角の鉄板何だからこちらでちょうどいい焼き加減で食したいんだけどなぁ。
reviews.translated_snippet:
My companion and I ordered skirt steak from the lunch menu, but the presentation of the salad and miso soup varied widely.
To be honest, the miso soup was too salty and the ingredients were overcooked.
I'm surprised that other people can eat without worrying.
In the past, you could enjoy yakiniku for lunch by preparing individual roasters, but at the time I went there, everything was served teppanyaki style, and if the timing wasn't right, the restaurant would be filled with smoke. Fortunately, the staff are all cheerful and kind, and the meal is pleasant, but the environment and seasoning are a bit of a deductible.
Most of the lunch menu is served on a griddle, and all the meat and vegetables are cooked until charred.
Since it's a hot iron plate, I'd like to eat it here with just the right amount of doneness.

place_info.title: すし松 東新宿店
place_info.address: Japan, 〒160-0022 Tokyo, Shinjuku City, Shinjuku, 7 Chome−27−6 COERU東新宿 2階

reviews.snippet:
他の方のコメントを見て初めて伺いましたが、予想通り予約してから食事するのに問題あり。
予約機は店外に設置するとかネットで事前予約するなど対策山積み。
車椅子で来た客が可哀想になった。
あと16番席はトイレの前だしごった返す入口前で、店員の大きな声の側で、全く落ち着いて食事出来ず雰囲気悪い席だった。
肝心の味の方は、赤身が価格的にオススメだったかな。
最後のシメで頼むお新香巻は沢庵は乾燥しきっていて最悪。
しかし海苔は有明産の風味と甘味にパリパリ感が残っている巻物だったのが救い。
オープンして間もないので、しばらくして様子見かな。
改善される良いお店になる事に期待します。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I came here for the first time after reading other people's comments, but as expected, there was a problem with making a reservation and then eating.
Many measures have been taken, such as installing reservation machines outside stores and making advance reservations online.
I felt sorry for the customer who came in a wheelchair.
Also, seat 16 was in front of the restroom, in front of the crowded entrance, and next to the loud voices of the staff, so I couldn't eat in peace at all, and the atmosphere was bad.
For those who are looking for the most important taste, I would recommend lean meat for the price.
The pickled rice roll I ordered at the end of the meal was dry and the worst.
However, the saving grace was that the seaweed was a roll that had the flavor and sweetness from Ariake and still had a crispy feel.
It hasn't been open for a while, so I'll wait and see what happens.
I hope that it will improve and become a good store.

place_info.title: Shinbashi New Tomochin Ramen
place_info.address: 新橋駅前ビル1号館 B1 2 Chome-20-15 Shinbashi, Minato City, Tokyo 105-0004, Japan

reviews.snippet:
750円の価格でライスも付いてお代わり出来れば、行列するのも分かる。
それにチャーシューは1枚ではなく数枚乗せられてるし食べ応えあります。
しかし麺硬をリクエストしたら店主曰く、スープとの相性上、硬めは受けられないと断れた…。
だって茹で揚げはタイマーで設定したテボが自動で湯切りするからなのかなと思った。
因みに茹で時間は2分30秒。

まぁ結果的には優しい味付けのしょうゆラーメンで美味しかったので文句無し。
昼は軽く20人ぐらい並ぶので、朝行くべし。
肝心のカウンター席は全部で6〜7名ぐらいだから仕方がない。
reviews.translated_snippet:
If the price of 750 yen comes with rice and you can refill it, I can see why there would be a line.
Also, there are not just one slice of chashu on top, but several slices on top, making it very satisfying to eat.
However, when I requested hard noodles, the owner said that he could not accept harder noodles because it would go well with the soup.
I thought it was because the boiling water was set on a timer and the water was automatically drained.
By the way, the boiling time is 2 minutes and 30 seconds.

Well, in the end, it was a mildly seasoned soy sauce ramen that was delicious, so I have no complaints.
There's a line of about 20 people at noon, so it's best to go in the morning.
It can't be helped because the important counter seats are only for 6-7 people in total.

place_info.title: Hayama
place_info.address: 1 Ichigayayakuojimachi, Shinjuku City, Tokyo 162-0063, Japan

reviews.snippet:
コロナ禍から長くお店は休業してたが、やっと待ちに待った再営業。
以前と変わらずお店は3人のカウンターと4人のカウンター席があります。タイミングが悪いと並ぶ。
ラーメンは単価が上がったが味は変わらず。でも個性的なパンチのある煮干しの風味が丸くなった気がしたのは、私が歳取って味覚が落ちたのかな？
再営業後待ちに待った味わい深いメンマが無く、盛るのを忘れたのかと隣の人の出来上がったラーメンを見たらやっぱりメンマが無く、すごく気になったが、聞きづらい雰囲気は昔と変わらない。
混んでなければ、以前は店主と気軽に話は出来たんだけど、その時はメンマの仕入れの苦労話を聞き、食材に拘っている姿勢に魅力を感じたんだけど、そのメンマが無く残念だったけど、また安定した仕入れが出来て復活されるのを楽しみにしたいと思います。
reviews.translated_snippet:
The store has been closed for a long time due to the coronavirus pandemic, but it has finally reopened.
As before, the store has counter seats for 3 people and counter seats for 4 people. Line up at bad timing.
The price of ramen has increased, but the taste remains the same. However, I felt that the flavor of the dried sardines, which had a unique punch, had become more rounded, perhaps because I had gotten older and my taste buds had deteriorated.
After reopening, the delicious menma noodles that I had been waiting for were missing, and when I looked at the person next to me's finished ramen, wondering if I had forgotten to put it on, there was no menma, which really bothered me, but the atmosphere was still the same as before.
If it wasn't crowded, I used to be able to have a casual conversation with the owner, but at that time, I heard about the hardships of purchasing menma, and I was impressed by their commitment to the ingredients.I was disappointed that they didn't have the menma, but I'm looking forward to it being revived with a stable supply of menma.

reviews.snippet:
落ち着いた店内は高級感あってちょっとした優越感を感じながら食せた。

The calm interior had a luxurious feel, and I ate with a slight sense of superiority.

I was also surprised by the variety of broths and ingredients available for the pork soup set.

Mansei is the best, as expected.

I was full, so I couldn't order the Mankatsu sandwich to take away 😭

place_info.address: 3Q2G+24R西北方向160米 169, Jinzhou District, Dalian, Liaoning, China, 116699

reviews.snippet:
この経済区内で少数で気軽に日本食以外で夕飯を済ませるところを探してみたら、口コミで5の評価。

迷わずお店に直行したら、入口は狭く、デリバリーピザ屋かと思ってしまう外観。

お国柄GoogleMAPには店内や食事の写真が掲載されていないので、思い切って扉を開けて入店。

19時前後に行ったら誰もお客さん居なく、愛想の良い男性スタッフが1名。

その後日本人の男性と現地の女性の2人連れが2組来店してたが、恐らく出張者や駐在員が訪れるお店なのかなと思う。

また？厨房にコックが居るのかは分からなったが、ピザやステーキ、パスタなど色々なメニューをオーダーしたらどれも絶品。

しかしパスタの茹で加減はお国柄なのかなと思った程度。

たくさん写真を撮ったので、近辺で夕飯を探している方は是非立ち寄ってみてください。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I was looking for a casual, non-Japanese place for dinner with just a few people in the economic zone, and I found this place with a 5-star rating.

I headed straight for the restaurant without hesitation, but the entrance was narrow and the exterior made me think it was a pizza delivery place.

Due to the country's unique characteristics, Google Maps doesn't have photos of the interior or the food, so I took a chance and opened the door and went inside.

When I arrived around 7pm, there were no customers, just one friendly male staff member.

Afterwards, two other couples, a Japanese man and a local woman, came in, and I think this is probably a place frequented by business travelers or expatriates.

Again? I couldn't tell if there was a chef in the kitchen, but the various dishes we ordered, including pizza, steak, and pasta, were all excellent.

However, I thought the way the pasta was cooked might be a reflection of the country's culture.

I took lots of photos, so if you're looking for dinner in the area, I recommend stopping by.

reviews.snippet:

place_info.title: Hamburg & Steak HASUNUMA
place_info.address: 270 Minamihasunuma, Misato, Saitama 341-0028, Japan

reviews.snippet:
どうやら過去はチェーン店から独立店になったお店。
駐車場の路面や店内の古びて、ｈメンテナンスまで行き届いていない否めない感があるが、お客さんへの満足度を高める商品の提供への努力をすごく感じた。
しかしハンバーグは、ファーストフードの成形パテっぽさ。
しかしステーキは値段以上の美味しさ。
オマケにサラダバーの豊富さとビーフカレーはお肉が柔らかく、カレー店かと思ってしまう味。
その為、絶対ランチの時間帯に利用するのがオススメ。
チェーン店風だけどやっぱ違いのあるお店。
三郷の人達が羨ましい…
reviews.translated_snippet:
It seems this shop was once a chain restaurant before it became independent.
The surface of the parking lot and the interior of the restaurant are old and there's an undeniable sense that it hasn't been well maintained, but I really felt that they're making an effort to provide products that will increase customer satisfaction.
However, the hamburger tasted like a pre-formed patty from a fast food restaurant.
The steak, however, was more than worth the price.
There's also an extensive salad bar and the beef curry was so tender you'd think it was at a curry restaurant.
For this reason, I definitely recommend going during lunch hours.
It has a chain feel to it, but it really is a restaurant with a difference.
I envy the people of Misato...

But apparently it's a popular restaurant where people line up even on rainy days.
You can choose from two flavors of motsunabe, so you should try them both.

Also, you should order horse sashimi and sesame mackerel before eating the hot pot.

place_info.title: Hotel Eclair Hakata
place_info.address: 1-1 Susakimachi, Hakata Ward, Fukuoka, 812-0028, Japan

reviews.snippet:
コメントに部屋は狭いと記載されて実際に泊まってみたら、都心のビジネスホテル並みのコンパクトな室内。
外観は小洒落た感じだけど、室内は普通のビジネスホテル。
繁華街から離れた静かな場所は良い。
近くには選べるほどの飲食店は見当たらないけど不便さはない。
コンビニはローソンが近くにあるけど、目の前の距離ではない。

タバコを吸う人は全館内は禁煙なので要注意。
吸いたい場合は1階のエレベーター裏の裏口出たところに灰皿があります。
reviews.translated_snippet:
A comment said that the room was small, so when I actually stayed there, I found the room to be as compact as a business hotel in the middle of the city.
It looks stylish from the outside, but inside it's a normal business hotel.
A quiet location away from downtown is good.
There aren't many restaurants to choose from nearby, but it's not an inconvenience.
There's a Lawson convenience store nearby, but it's not right in front of me.

If you smoke, please be careful as smoking is prohibited in the entire building.
If you want to smoke, there is an ashtray on the first floor, just outside the back door behind the elevator.

place_info.title: Kamukura Dining - atré Ebisu
place_info.address: Japan, 〒150-0022 Tokyo, Shibuya, Ebisuminami, 1 Chome−5−5 atre恵比寿2F

reviews.snippet:
やっぱこの味に戻ってしまう。
久しぶりに食事に行ったら入り口のタブレットで席が決められてしまうシステムに動揺。
まぁ味は変わらず体に染みる味は安心感ハンパない。
ただ麺の硬めのリクエストは態々店員を呼ばないとダメなのがめんどい。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I always end up going back to this taste.
When I went to eat there for the first time in a while, I was confused by the system where your seat is assigned by a tablet at the entrance.
But the taste hasn't changed and the flavor soaks into your body is incredibly comforting.
However, it's a hassle that you have to call a waiter over if you want firmer noodles.

response.snippet:
この度はどうとんぼり神座 アトレ恵比寿店をご利用いただき、誠にありがとうございます。変わらぬ味をお楽しみいただけたとのこと、大変嬉しく思います。

新しい座席システムについてはご不便をおかけし、申し訳ございません。お客様により快適にお過ごしいただけるよう導入いたしましたが、今後改善の余地がないか検討させていただきます。

麺の硬さのリクエストに関しては、ご指摘ありがとうございます。より便利にお客様のご要望にお応えできるよう、システムの改善を検討いたします。

今後もお客様にご満足いただけるよう努めてまいります。またのご来店を心よりお待ちしております。
response.translated_snippet:
Thank you for visiting Dotonbori Kamizura Atre Ebisu. We are very pleased to hear that you enjoyed our unchanged flavor. 

We apologize for any inconvenience caused by the new seating system. We introduced it to provide a more comfortable experience for our customers, and we will continue to consider whether there is room for improvement in the future. 

Thank you for pointing out your request for noodle firmness. We will consider improving our system so that we can more conveniently meet your needs. 

We will continue to strive to satisfy our customers, and we look forward to seeing you again.

place_info.title: PRIMO PASSO
place_info.address: Heights Ms, 1F 2 Chome-6-7 Haramachi, Shinjuku City, Tokyo 162-0053, Japan

reviews.snippet:
ランチのサラダはボリュームがあって大満足。
オリジナルのドレッシングも旨味たっぷりの味。
ランチのパスタは3種類から選べる。
味も量も満足できるけど、席の案内などホスピタリティは低めだったかな。
若い女性が一人でランチしに来て、席は沢山空いているのに、二人組の若い男性客の隣の席に誘導するのは可哀想に見えた。
雰囲気や食以外を気にしないで食事を楽しめる人には問題なく楽しめると思う。
タイミング次第かもしれないが、パスタは美味しかったので空いている時を見計らってまた伺いたいです。
reviews.translated_snippet:
The lunch salad is voluminous and very satisfying.
The original dressing is also full of flavor.
You can choose from three types of pasta for lunch.
I was satisfied with the taste and quantity, but I think the hospitality, including seating guidance, was poor.
It seemed pathetic for a young woman to come to lunch alone and have to lead her to a seat next to two young male customers even though there were plenty of empty seats.
I think people who can enjoy a meal without worrying about things other than the atmosphere and food will have no problem enjoying it.
It might depend on the timing, but the pasta was delicious, so I'd like to visit again when it's free.

reviews.snippet:

ウォシュレットの便座は後付けなのか便器と一体感がなく蓋はしゃがむ時に蓋が閉じるので大変使い難い有り様。
救いだったのはマットレスが英国の有名なメーカーの物を使用し枕も週種類から選べるので睡眠は満足。
あと朝食のシェフ自慢?のハンバーグは期待を裏切るガッカリなものだった。(評価厳しいかな)
reviews.translated_snippet:
The breakfast is satisfying, but the room is small and a bit old.
The washlet toilet seat is probably an afterthought, but it doesn't feel integrated with the toilet bowl, and the lid closes when you squat down, making it very difficult to use.
The saving grace was that the mattress was made by a famous British manufacturer, and the pillows could be chosen from a variety of different types, so I was satisfied with my sleep.
Also, the chef's signature hamburger steak for breakfast was a disappointment. (Perhaps the evaluation is harsh)

details.rooms:
狭い。
スーツケース広げる余裕がない。
トイレの便座はしゃがむ度に蓋が閉まるので非常に不便でムカつく。

translated_details.rooms:
It's cramped.
There's no room to open your suitcase.
The toilet seat lid closes every time you squat down, which is extremely inconvenient and annoying.

response.snippet:
この度はホテルサンルートソプラ神戸にご宿泊頂きまして誠にありがとうございます。
朝食につきましては当ホテルの自慢のぼっかけからホテル特製のチーズバーガー等取り揃えており、期間限定で様々な新メニューを出しておりますがチーズバーガーにはご満足いただけませんでした様で残念にございます。お写真を拝見しましたところお正月メニューをお召し上がり頂いた様ですので、機会があれば違う時期のメニューもご賞味いただければ幸いです。
睡眠につきましても仰られます通り寝具には力を注いでおります事に加え、ホテル周辺は繁華街からは少々離れておりますがその分閑静でお休みいただきやすい環境にございます。
しかしながらトイレ設備ではご迷惑をおかけしまして申し訳ございません。お客様からのご申告や清掃スタッフからの報告等を受けましたら、交換等を行っておりますが、対応が及ばず満足いくご滞在に出来ず心苦しく思っております。
誠に勝手ではございますが次回神戸にお越しの際には挽回の機会を頂けますと僥倖でございます。
お忙しい中、ご投稿ありがとうございました。
response.translated_snippet:
Thank you for staying at Hotel Sunroute Sopra Kobe.

For breakfast, we have a variety of new menu items, from our hotel's signature bokkake to our hotel's special cheeseburger, and we are sorry that you were not satisfied with the cheeseburger. From what I saw in the photo, it seems that you enjoyed the New Year's menu, so we hope that you will enjoy the menu for a different season if you have the opportunity.

As for sleep, as you said, we put a lot of effort into the bedding, and although the area around the hotel is a little far from the downtown area, it is a quiet environment where you can rest comfortably.

However, we apologize for the inconvenience caused by the toilet facilities. When we receive reports from customers and reports from cleaning staff, we replace them, but we are sorry that we were unable to respond and were unable to provide a satisfactory stay.

We apologize for the inconvenience, but we would be happy if you could give us a chance to make up for it the next time you visit Kobe.

Thank you for taking the time to post your review.

place_info.title: Sawayaka
place_info.address: 8912-2 Gioncho, Shimada, Shizuoka 427-0058, Japan

reviews.snippet:
やっとの思いで訪れたお店。
期待して長時間待って頼んだハンバーグにはびっくり。
関東圏でお馴染みの大俵バーグや爆弾ハンバーグに近い物かと思ったら表面はコンガリだけど中はモロ生肉。
最初の一口目はハンバーグと言うよりもソーセージの食感とイメージが湧き、肉々しいハンバーグ感は全くなし。

これがここの売りでオススメなのか尋ねたけど、何故炭火で焼いてあの程度のハンバーグなのか素直に美味しいとは感じず只々何で皆高い評価するのか不思議でならなかった。

しかし脇役のサラダは各野菜の鮮度と旨味を感じ、味噌汁も最高だった。

救いだったのはアキバ系っぽいお姉さんの接客の素晴らしさが光っていた。

しかし都内からここ迄向かって事前に予約の出来ないこのチェーン店にはもう行く魅力も無い感じ。
reviews.translated_snippet:
Finally, I visited this restaurant.
I was surprised by the hamburg steak I ordered after waiting a long time with high expectations.
I thought it would be similar to the Otawara Burger or Bomb Hamburger that are popular in the Kanto region, but the surface was crispy but the inside was raw meat.
At the first bite, it had the texture and image of a sausage rather than a hamburger steak, and it had no meaty hamburger feel at all.
I asked if this was their selling point and recommended, but I honestly didn't think it was tasty considering it was grilled over charcoal, and I was simply wondering why everyone was rating it so highly.

However, the side salad had the freshness and flavor of each vegetable, and the miso soup was also excellent.

The saving grace was the excellent customer service provided by the Akihabara-like lady.

However, it seems there is no point going to this chain restaurant, which you can't make a reservation for in advance, even though it's all the way here from Tokyo.

reviews.snippet:

餃子や定食類はオススメです。

ラーメンは、中国にある日本式居酒屋にあるような微妙なものだった。

チャーハンは、炒め過ぎで米粒がパサついて焦げ目が多い。
おまけに味付けが超薄くて何食ってんのか分かんない品。

野菜炒めは、塩気が強くて眉間にシワが出来るありさま。

兎に角、味と質が落ちた。
残念。
reviews.translated_snippet:
The seasoning is absolutely delicious.
I recommend the gyoza and set meals.
The above is from last year.

Everything I ate today was terrible.
The ramen was mediocre, like the kind you'd find in a Japanese-style izakaya in China.

The fried rice was overcooked, so the rice was dry and heavily burnt.

On top of that, the seasoning was so light that you couldn't even tell what you were eating.

The stir-fried vegetables were so salty that it made your brow crease.

In short, the taste and quality have gone down.

What a shame.

place_info.title: 長崎チャンポン 百万石
place_info.address: Japan, 〒338-0837 Saitama, Sakura Ward, Tajima, 1 Chome−5−8 長崎チャンポン百万石

reviews.snippet:
数年ぶりに訪れたけど休日の夜は意外と混んでて並ぶ。
お店の前に駐車場があったけど、今は離れたところに3台分の駐車場が用意されている様子。

相変わらずちゃんぽんは物凄い海鮮臭。(いい意味で)
よって、ちゃんぽんチェーン店とは別格。
しかし味は美味しいけど野菜は炒め過ぎで過ぎかな。
チャーハンも味はちょい濃い目で味わい深いけどお米はパラパラと言うよりもべちゃ気味だった。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I visited there for the first time in a few years, and it was surprisingly crowded on a holiday night and there were lines.
There used to be a parking lot in front of the store, but now there seems to be a parking lot for 3 cars in a separate area.

Champon still has a strong seafood smell. (in a good way)
Therefore, it is different from Champon chain stores.
However, although the taste was delicious, the vegetables were overcooked.
The fried rice was also a bit strong and flavorful, but the rice was more soggy than dry.

details.recommended_dishes: 長崎ちゃんぽんとチャーハン
details.parking: お店の通りの反対側に3台分しか駐められない。

translated_details.parking: There is only parking for 3 cars on the opposite side of the street from the store.

place_info.title: レストラン モン
place_info.address: Japan, 〒162-0056 Tokyo, Shinjuku City, Wakamatsucho, 9−9 パークホームズ 2F

reviews.snippet:
ランチの満足感はあったけど、ハンバーグなど個々の料理は今ひとつ。
しかし場所柄、この辺でこの価格の洋食ランチが楽しめるところがないので貴重な存在のお店だと思う。
reviews.translated_snippet:
The lunch was satisfying, but the individual dishes, such as the hamburger steak, were a bit lacking. 
However, due to its location, there aren't many places around here where you can enjoy a Western-style lunch at this price, so I think this is a valuable restaurant.

details.recommended_dishes: ハンバーグとカニクリームコロッケランチ

place_info.title: SAN TORA
place_info.address: プレステージ３６２ 1階 362 Yamabukicho, Shinjuku City, Tokyo 162-0801, Japan

reviews.snippet:
期待して並んで食べましたけど、満足感はそこそこだったかな。

仕込みやこだわりはテレビで拝見しましたけど、確かに美味しい味噌ラーメン。
次回は醤油を試してみたいかな。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I lined up and ate with high expectations, but I guess I was only pretty satisfied.

I've seen the preparation and attention to detail on TV, and it's definitely delicious miso ramen.
I think I'd like to try soy sauce next time.

place_info.title: Yoshinoya
place_info.address: 1 Chome-30-1 Asakusabashi, Taito City, Tokyo 111-0053, Japan

reviews.snippet:
以前の店舗スタイルと異なり、一言も話さずオーダー出来て全てセルフ。
今まで頼み難かった独自のアレンジで食したい人には良いかも。
reviews.translated_snippet:
Unlike the previous store style, you can order without speaking a word and everything is self-service.
It might be good for people who want to eat with their own unique arrangement, which was difficult to order before.

place_info.title: Zenzo Sakai Store
place_info.address: Japan, 〒173-0016 Tokyo, Itabashi City, Nakaitabashi, 15−13 坂井善三商店 水曜日営業の日もあります。https://zenzo.tokyo/free/calendar でご確認ください。

reviews.snippet:
買い物途中にふらっと店内を覗き程度だったんだけど、店員さんがスッと試食を勧められ漬物を試食。
思わずぬか漬けを購入。
やっぱりスーパーで買うより専門店で買うのは美味しいなぁって感じちゃう。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I just popped into the store while I was shopping, but the staff member quickly offered me a sample of some pickles, so I did. 
I couldn't help but buy some pickled vegetables in rice bran. 
I really feel that pickles taste better when bought at a specialty store than at the supermarket.

response.snippet:
hiroshi s さま、ご来店ありがとうございました。
★を5つも！　光栄です！
お口に合って良かったです。
どうぞまたお寄り下さい。お待ちしております。
response.translated_snippet:
Thank you for visiting us, Hiroshi S.
Five stars! What an honor!
I'm glad you enjoyed it.
Please come visit us again. We look forward to seeing you.

place_info.title: Ando
place_info.address: 安藤ビル B-1 14-10 Nakaitabashi, Itabashi City, Tokyo 173-0016, Japan

reviews.snippet:
santoku(三徳)スーパーと板橋の無印良品内に一品だけお煎餅を扱っている米菓のお店。
初めて伺ったけど種類の豊富さにテンション上がる。
お店の前には特価品がありまとめ買いしたら、会計時におまけを貰った。
ここの煎餅は焼き加減とタレが絶品。
reviews.translated_snippet:
A rice cracker shop that only sells rice crackers inside Santoku Supermarket and Muji in Itabashi.
It was my first time visiting, but I was excited by the variety of varieties.
There were special deals in front of the store, so I bought them in bulk and got a bonus when I checked out.
The rice crackers here are perfectly grilled and the sauce is exquisite.

place_info.title: Komeda's Coffee Asakusabashi Station
place_info.address: VORT 浅草橋駅前 ２階, 1 Chome-20-4 Yanagibashi, Taito City, Tokyo 111-0052, Japan

reviews.snippet:
ランチ目当てで行ったみたけど飲み物と食事で軽く1,000円超え。
おまけにランチ時間帯を避けて行ってみても長居する客が多くて休憩時間内でゆっくりすることができない有り様。
ガッカリしたランチだった😢
reviews.translated_snippet:
I went there for lunch, but the cost of a meal and drink easily exceeded 1,000 yen.

Even if I went outside the lunch hours, there were many customers who stayed for a long time, so I couldn't relax during the break.

It was a disappointing lunch😢

place_info.address: 1326-1 Maekawa, Itako, Ibaraki 311-2416, Japan

reviews.snippet:
絶対におにぎりを頼んでほしい。
お味噌汁と卵焼きも絶品。
値段がお手頃なので、絶対に満足する筈です。
reviews.translated_snippet:
You should definitely order the onigiri.
The miso soup and tamagoyaki are also excellent.
The price is reasonable, so you're sure to be satisfied.

place_info.title: Kaizantei Itchō Kitamoto
place_info.address: 6 Chome-125 Nakamaru, Kitamoto, Saitama 364-0013, Japan

reviews.snippet:
店舗内の雰囲気は良いけど料理は多種多彩だけどメニューの写真と現物の違いにガッカリするものが多々あり。
17時以降になると日中はオーダーできないラーメンや単品メニューがあるようです。
reviews.translated_snippet:
The atmosphere inside the restaurant is nice and there is a wide variety of food, but there are many disappointing dishes that look different from the photos on the menu. 
After 5pm, there are some ramen and a la carte dishes that cannot be ordered during the day.

Maybe it was because of the TV or the heat, but the shops and inside the building were overflowing with people.

place_info.title: Seafoods Restaurant Mexico - Tsukuba Flamingo
place_info.address: 3362 Ozone, Tsukuba, Ibaraki 300-3253, Japan

reviews.snippet:
テレビを観てからずっと気になっていたお店。
都内にもお店があるようだがフラミンゴ見たさに近くのお参りを兼ねて伺いました。
昭和感漂う雰囲気は心地良さを感じる。
食事に至ってはカニピラフとタンとビーフシチューを注文。
カニピラフは殻付きと剥いたものが選択可。
独自の味付けしたピラフは絶品だったが、アクセントにしていると思えるピーマンは必要以上に苦みが気になった。
せめて冷水で一晩漬けたピーマンを使用してくれれば甘みと食感が増してグレードアップするんじゃないのかなと思った。
シチューはタンの方がおすすめ。
双方とも赤ワインをふんだんに使用しているのを感じる味と風味。ビーフはスジ肉を使用しているせいか脂身が多過ぎで口に入れられなかった。
しかしどちらの肉もトコトン煮込んでいるので食べやすかった。
reviews.translated_snippet:
I had been interested in this restaurant ever since I saw it on TV.
There seems to be a store in Tokyo, but I went here to see the flamingos and to visit a nearby shrine.
The atmosphere reminiscent of the Showa era is very comfortable.
For the food, I ordered crab pilaf, tongue, and beef stew.
You can choose crab pilaf with or without the shell.
The pilaf, which was seasoned with a unique flavor, was excellent, but the green peppers, which I thought were used as an accent, were more bitter than necessary.
I thought that if they had at least used green peppers that had been soaked in cold water overnight, the sweetness and texture would have been increased and it would have been upgraded.
For the stew, I would recommend the tongue.
Both dishes had a taste and flavor that made me realize that they used a lot of red wine. The beef was too fatty, probably because it used tendon meat, and I couldn't eat it.
However, both meats were thoroughly cooked, so it was easy to eat.

details.recommended_dishes: カニピラフ 殻付き
